//This master thesis researches a new way of making in architecture: 
 In #experiment01-Triangular-Vault the feasibility of using snow as formwork material is tested. #experiment02 Happy Accidents explores possibilities and chance of shaping snow. With field trips #research Heinz Isler the history of natural form finding is explored. The technical advantages are analysed in #experiment05 Melt Out. Concrete behaviour in cold environments is tested in the #experiment06 Concrete Laboratory. Inaccuracies of snow as formwork material are taken into account in #experiment07 Curtain Arch. #experiment08 1 to 100 explores a manual way for producing digitally. The process is executed in #experiment09 Rock Pavilion. Possibilities are taken further at #experiment10 Glaspass. A summary about #natural formations. Previous structural knowledge with ice was gained in #The Ice Shell Project. #About the participants. 
 See the story in the #movie The Accurate Inaccurate//
